e counter-term, which is universal in this model and\nalways with negative sign. $\\delta_{hZZ}^{(1)}$ is independent of the sign of\n$\\lambda_{\\Phi{S}}$ and its typical size is $-0.2\\%\\sim-2\\%$. When combining\n$hhh$ and $hZZ$ precision measurements together, parameter space of this model\ncan be probed well including the sign and size of $\\lambda_{\\Phi{S}}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 15 Jul 2016 13:12:56 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 31 Jul 2016 02:28:42 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 24 Jun 2019 08:31:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-06-25"}
