can be trapped in one of the atoms, and sometimes in all\natoms indicating that at these small distances the system decays to a state for\nwhich there are no radiative modes available for emission.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 15 Jul 2016 14:16:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-11-23"}
